WEBVTT

00:03.371 --> 00:04.938
Dad, I didn't get
the fellowship.

00:04.938 --> 00:06.006
You still believe in me,
though, right?

00:06.006 --> 00:06.939
He knew, didn't he?

00:06.939 --> 00:08.209
Zoe, I can explain.

00:08.209 --> 00:09.310
What's there to explain?

00:09.310 --> 00:10.878
Why Harley left
me the practice?

00:10.878 --> 00:12.313
Why Dad stopped loving me?

00:12.313 --> 00:14.448
I was trying to get over
someone, and I shouldn't

00:14.448 --> 00:16.149
have dated, but I wanted
to, because I like you.

00:16.149 --> 00:18.252
DIDI: No one knows what's gonna
 happen between two people.

00:18.252 --> 00:20.754
Until yesterday,
 I was having such a good time.

00:20.754 --> 00:23.357
He's hung up on someone, and
I think that someone is Lemon.

00:23.357 --> 00:25.526
Didi has been avoiding me
because she found this.

00:25.526 --> 00:27.495
Oh, my God. You have
got to keep this secret.

00:27.495 --> 00:29.130
Look, Didi, the picture's mine.

00:29.130 --> 00:30.631
I'm just so relieved!

00:30.631 --> 00:32.366
I am driving to
Mobile to pick up

00:32.366 --> 00:34.768
fabric for the bridesmaids
dresses, I meeting with the

00:34.768 --> 00:36.937
the caterer, I'm gonna reconfirm
our block of rooms at the...

00:36.937 --> 00:39.006
Okay, okay, you know what?
That's way too much stuff.

00:39.006 --> 00:41.342
We shouldn't be sitting here,
waiting and planning.

00:41.342 --> 00:43.711
That's not life, George.
What are you saying?

00:43.711 --> 00:45.113
Let's elope.

00:46.147 --> 00:48.048
* *

00:55.256 --> 00:58.359
Hey! Come back here!

00:58.359 --> 01:00.561
I'm gonna get you.

01:01.562 --> 01:03.497
(splat)

01:03.497 --> 01:04.965
Hey!

01:04.965 --> 01:06.167
Wait for me!

01:06.167 --> 01:07.535
Yeah, you'd better run.

01:07.535 --> 01:11.872
Hey. Finally, BlueBell
does something right. Snow!

01:11.872 --> 01:14.175
Look, it's
so pretty!

01:14.175 --> 01:15.843
I can't see pretty.

01:15.843 --> 01:17.645
I can only see doom.

01:17.645 --> 01:20.080
Only snows in BlueBell
every once in a while.

01:20.080 --> 01:22.150
When it does,
bad things happen.

01:22.150 --> 01:24.552
Last time, we had
our first-ever traffic jam.

01:24.552 --> 01:28.389
Fire broke out in the mystery
section of the library.

01:28.389 --> 01:30.258
We lost our whole
James Patterson collection.

01:30.258 --> 01:32.593
So, how does snow cause a fire?

01:32.593 --> 01:34.862
'Cause the fool librarian
busted out space heaters

01:34.862 --> 01:37.998
that hadn't been used since
Lady Bird Johnson was in town.

01:37.998 --> 01:40.033
Burt Reynolds was freezing.

01:40.033 --> 01:41.502
I bought him some boots,

01:41.502 --> 01:44.305
but they turned out
to be made of alligator, so...

01:44.305 --> 01:46.140
And then, of course,
today, of all days,

01:46.140 --> 01:47.975
my parents decide
to fly in from Houston

01:47.975 --> 01:49.277
and surprise me with a visit.

01:49.277 --> 01:51.078
What?!
Yeah.

01:51.078 --> 01:52.580
Big day for Lavon Hayes!

01:52.580 --> 01:54.582
Parents meeting the girlfriend.
Whoa.

01:54.582 --> 01:56.384
Hey, don't you think
it's a little early

01:56.384 --> 01:57.818
for her to meet the parents?

01:57.818 --> 01:59.052
Have you met Didi?

01:59.052 --> 02:00.988
The woman is a delight.

02:00.988 --> 02:05.226
My mama has been worried about
my lack of a significant other.

02:05.226 --> 02:07.161
They've been wanting me
to settle down.

02:07.161 --> 02:08.862
So, you and Didi
are settling down?

02:08.862 --> 02:11.365
We're not settling down.
I'm just saying,

02:11.365 --> 02:12.566
I'm ready to commit.

02:12.566 --> 02:15.436
So, yeah...

02:15.436 --> 02:18.206
we are getting serious.

02:18.206 --> 02:21.041
Well... okay.
Good for you.

02:21.041 --> 02:24.077
Hope you're gonna come
to dinner, too, meet my parents?

02:24.077 --> 02:25.346
I wouldn't miss it, just as long

02:25.346 --> 02:27.114
as I don't have
to sit next to Wade.

02:27.114 --> 02:29.383
When are y'all gonna make up?

02:29.383 --> 02:31.018
When that spineless infant
apologizes

02:31.018 --> 02:33.187
for breaking up me and Judson.

02:33.187 --> 02:34.555
I'll see you later.

02:34.555 --> 02:35.823
Be careful.

02:35.823 --> 02:36.957
(scoffs)

02:36.957 --> 02:40.628
Lavon! It's just... snow!

02:42.230 --> 02:44.064
I'm okay!

02:44.064 --> 02:48.236
Let me just say:
BlueBell snow-- bad.

02:48.236 --> 02:49.870
Now, I know
it's your fishing day, Marv,

02:49.870 --> 02:52.240
but did you even check
if the bay was frozen

02:52.240 --> 02:53.541
before stepping out
on the ice?

02:53.541 --> 02:55.409
Ice is invisible, Brick.

02:55.409 --> 02:57.110
You can't see it.

02:57.110 --> 02:59.480
Hey, Addy?

02:59.480 --> 03:01.081
Mm?
I am expecting

03:01.081 --> 03:02.250
an important phone call
from Germany,

03:02.250 --> 03:04.218
so be sure to get me
when it comes in.

03:04.218 --> 03:05.986
Oh, who do you know
in Germany?
My dad.

03:05.986 --> 03:07.888
Your dad?

03:07.888 --> 03:10.424
Oh. Uh, yeah, I remembered
it was his birthday,

03:10.424 --> 03:12.760
so I sent him his favorite
macaroons from Paris.

03:12.760 --> 03:14.628
He'll be calling
to say thanks.

03:14.628 --> 03:16.764
I left the office number
and my cell

03:16.764 --> 03:18.332
on the return slip.

03:18.332 --> 03:20.534
What kind of father doesn't know
his own daughter's phone number?

03:20.534 --> 03:22.503
Well, he's very busy.

03:22.503 --> 03:24.672
You know, he's the top
cardiothoracic surgeon

03:24.672 --> 03:27.941
in Europe, and they smoke a lot
over there, so you can imagine.

03:27.941 --> 03:30.344
ADDY:
Well, also, there's
that difficult discussion

03:30.344 --> 03:31.545
you've both been avoiding.

03:31.545 --> 03:34.282
The one about how
you finally discovered

03:34.282 --> 03:36.317
you're not biologically related.

03:36.317 --> 03:38.719
Mm, yeah, and that.

03:38.719 --> 03:41.021
BRICK:
Sounds like the man
has purposely distanced

03:41.021 --> 03:42.556
himself a-a bit...

03:42.556 --> 03:44.191
He wasn't distancing himself
from me.

03:44.191 --> 03:46.026
He was distancing himself
from my mom

03:46.026 --> 03:47.895
and the pain
that she caused him.

03:47.895 --> 03:49.463
He's still my dad.

03:49.463 --> 03:52.165
You know, even though
we haven't spoken in a while,

03:52.165 --> 03:54.435
that's never gonna change.

03:54.435 --> 03:56.570
Well, I'll let you know
when he calls.

03:56.570 --> 03:58.972
WADE:
 Apologize to Zoe?

03:58.972 --> 04:01.041
Forget it. She's not
even nice to me.

04:01.041 --> 04:03.176
Well, at least be nice to her.

04:03.176 --> 04:05.379
My parents are meeting
Didi tonight.

04:05.379 --> 04:07.281
I don't need
any additional worries.

04:07.281 --> 04:09.483
Moms and Pops Hayes
are gonna love Didi.

04:09.483 --> 04:11.319
I mean, what's
not to love?

04:11.319 --> 04:12.886
I can't do it!
I can't...

04:12.886 --> 04:15.823
Whoa. Whoa, whoa.
What's going on?

04:15.823 --> 04:17.425
I can't meet your parents
on snow day!

04:17.425 --> 04:18.692
I've heard. I've heard
the terrible tales.

04:18.692 --> 04:20.494
They're gonna hate me,

04:20.494 --> 04:21.829
or we'll be electrocuted.

04:21.829 --> 04:22.996
Probably both!

04:22.996 --> 04:25.065
Didi, I know
the weather is foreboding now,

04:25.065 --> 04:26.199
but everything's gonna be fine.

04:26.199 --> 04:27.301
Well, you got
to understand.

04:27.301 --> 04:28.569
Lavon's parents
are, like,

04:28.569 --> 04:30.237
pretty much the coolest
people you ever met.

04:30.237 --> 04:32.873
His dad, Ernie,
is so funny.

04:32.873 --> 04:34.207
You guys should see
the impression

04:34.207 --> 04:35.343
he does of Little Wayne.

04:35.343 --> 04:37.745
I mean, it is...
Oh! And Carolyn?

04:37.745 --> 04:39.480
She's like the mom
you never had.

04:39.480 --> 04:42.182
But I have a mother.
She's amazing.

04:42.182 --> 04:43.851
Not really.
Not like Carolyn.

04:43.851 --> 04:45.486
Lavon,

04:45.486 --> 04:47.821
are you sure your parents
are going to like me?

04:47.821 --> 04:49.222
I am sure.

04:49.222 --> 04:50.624
Okay. Then I just realized

04:50.624 --> 04:52.793
I'm wearing
the totally wrong outfit.

04:52.793 --> 04:55.329
And I think I left my stove on.

04:55.329 --> 04:56.364
Whoa, whoa.

04:56.364 --> 04:58.666
Whoa. Whoa.
(laughing)

05:01.502 --> 05:04.972
They are gonna love her, right?

05:04.972 --> 05:07.441
Long as the snow lets up.

05:09.643 --> 05:11.745
LEMON:
 Okay, what about

05:11.745 --> 05:14.081
the tenth?
Uh-uh. I got to be
in court that Monday.

05:14.081 --> 05:16.450
Okay, and the weekend after,
I have my bachelorette party.

05:16.450 --> 05:17.685
If I cancelled,
everyone will know.

05:17.685 --> 05:20.354
Okay, well, then,
we have no choice.

05:20.354 --> 05:22.656
We're doing it today.
Today?! It's
snowing outside.

05:22.656 --> 05:24.358
Are you trying to
doom our marriage?

05:24.358 --> 05:26.360
Look, we are not
gonna be able to elope

05:26.360 --> 05:27.761
without this entire town
knowing about it,

05:27.761 --> 05:30.097
anyway, so I say,
we get out of town.

05:30.097 --> 05:31.632
I say we go somewhere,

05:31.632 --> 05:34.034
I say we have a nice,

05:34.034 --> 05:35.536
romantic night in a hotel...

05:35.536 --> 05:37.438
Mmm.
and we get married
tomorrow morning.

05:37.438 --> 05:39.673
Okay, now,
I've read in a magazine

05:39.673 --> 05:43.444
that Charleston is the number
two destination for weddings.

05:43.444 --> 05:44.778
Whoo! So spontaneous!

05:44.778 --> 05:46.947
I love it. I'm in, I'm in.

05:46.947 --> 05:49.216
Okay, babe, hold on.
Just... one second.

05:49.216 --> 05:52.920
I just want to make sure this is
really want you want to do.

05:52.920 --> 05:54.855
I just want you to know,
we can still have the wedding.

05:54.855 --> 05:57.324
You can still have
the white dress...

05:57.324 --> 05:59.292
Hey, George, all of the stress

05:59.292 --> 06:01.328
from this damn wedding
is killing us.

06:01.328 --> 06:03.564
I just want to marry you

06:03.564 --> 06:06.133
as fast as I can
in the first dress I find,

06:06.133 --> 06:10.070
and I don't care if it is white
or off-white or...

06:10.070 --> 06:12.773
ivory.

06:12.773 --> 06:14.642
(laughs)

06:18.446 --> 06:20.448
(sighs)

06:20.448 --> 06:22.416
Ooh!
Oh!

06:22.416 --> 06:23.851
Sorry I drove so slow.

06:23.851 --> 06:25.786
Can't take any
chances on a snow day.

06:25.786 --> 06:28.155
Well, it's not like
we're going to get stranded

06:28.155 --> 06:29.890
and have to eat each other, son.

06:29.890 --> 06:31.224
(laughs)
Oh.

06:31.224 --> 06:32.426
Oh, man.

06:32.426 --> 06:34.294
Oh, hey, y'all got
to hear my band.

06:34.294 --> 06:36.329
You know, we got a
bunch of new songs.

06:36.329 --> 06:38.599
We got one
called "Lightning."

06:38.599 --> 06:40.468
It's about a dog
who shows up

06:40.468 --> 06:41.835
in a lighting storm.

06:41.835 --> 06:43.504
Yeah, well, I don't want
to give too much away,

06:43.504 --> 06:44.572
but I can go grab my guitar.

06:44.572 --> 06:46.173
I'd be happy to play it for you.

06:46.173 --> 06:50.243
It sounds wonderful, Wade, but
right now, we're pretty tired.

06:50.243 --> 06:52.780
So, Dad, how are things going
at the Lavon Hayes Steakhouse?

06:52.780 --> 06:54.482
Amazing. It's the greatest gift

06:54.482 --> 06:55.883
I ever got.

06:55.883 --> 06:57.751
It's the one thing
in the world I can count on.

06:57.751 --> 06:59.887
I'm so sorry I'm late.

06:59.887 --> 07:01.555
I didn't want to drive
and end up in a snow drift

07:01.555 --> 07:05.158
and have to be rescued like in
that movie Misery, so I walked.

07:05.158 --> 07:09.029
Uh, Mom, Dad,
this is my girlfriend, Didi.

07:09.029 --> 07:11.765
Oh.
Didi, oh, honey,
it's so nice to meet you.

07:11.765 --> 07:13.534
Hi.
Well,
hello there, Didi.

07:13.534 --> 07:16.504
I have heard so much
about you both.

07:16.504 --> 07:18.972
Mr. Hayes, you have a
restaurant in Houston.

07:18.972 --> 07:20.340
I love... food.

07:20.340 --> 07:22.375
I eat it every day.

07:22.375 --> 07:23.811
And Mrs. Hayes,

07:23.811 --> 07:25.513
you were a teacher.
That's so great.

07:25.513 --> 07:27.748
What is it that they
say about teachers?

07:27.748 --> 07:30.684
"Those who can, do; those
who can't... teach."

07:30.684 --> 07:33.453
No, that's not
the right one.
(laughing)

07:33.453 --> 07:36.524
LAVON:
Anyway, we're just so glad
you decided to come for a visit.

07:36.524 --> 07:38.492
I mean, what
brings you to
town, though?

07:38.492 --> 07:39.827
I thought y'all
was waiting

07:39.827 --> 07:41.862
for your big 40th
anniversary next month.

07:43.831 --> 07:45.799
Uh, Lavon, if you wouldn't mind,

07:45.799 --> 07:48.869
your father and I would like
to speak to you in private.

07:50.804 --> 07:53.106
BRICK:
 All right, folks.

07:53.106 --> 07:54.908
Would you just listen up
here, please?

07:54.908 --> 07:56.677
Just stay inside today,
'cause we all know

07:56.677 --> 07:59.346
weird things are happening.

07:59.346 --> 08:00.781
The weird thing is

08:00.781 --> 08:03.083
how these people function
every other day of the year.

08:03.083 --> 08:04.852
Oh, hey, don't forget
I'm next, okay?

08:04.852 --> 08:05.318
Mm.

08:05.318 --> 08:07.154
(grunts)

08:07.154 --> 08:09.022
Oh.

08:09.022 --> 08:10.323
(ringtone playing)

08:10.323 --> 08:11.925
Hey, Lavon, can I call you back?

08:11.925 --> 08:14.962
I just wanted to let you know
there's no need to rush home.

08:14.962 --> 08:19.166
My parents just told me
they're...

08:19.166 --> 08:21.168
they're splitting up.

08:21.168 --> 08:23.470
Oh, Lavon, I am so sorry.

08:23.470 --> 08:25.472
Happy snow day, huh?

08:25.472 --> 08:26.874
(sighs)

08:26.874 --> 08:28.909
See?

08:35.347 --> 08:37.551
(seabirds chirping)

08:42.722 --> 08:43.857
DIDI:
 This is a terrible way

08:43.857 --> 08:45.192
to meet your parents.

08:45.192 --> 08:46.994
I wanted them to like me.
Now, I'm just

08:46.994 --> 08:49.129
a witness
to their marital disaster.

08:49.129 --> 08:51.531
Yeah, well, I wanted them
to like you, too, Didi.

08:51.531 --> 08:53.967
You know, my parents'
relationship always inspired me.

08:53.967 --> 08:56.904
I wanted them to see that
I could find happiness, too.

08:56.904 --> 08:57.871
Mm.

08:57.871 --> 08:59.306
It's just really bad timing.

08:59.306 --> 09:00.974
We have to help them.

09:00.974 --> 09:02.676
Sometimes, a couple
just needs a little nudge

09:02.676 --> 09:04.144
to remember how they feel
about each other.

09:04.144 --> 09:06.146
You and I forgot,
then you paraded

09:06.146 --> 09:08.115
prostitutes through town,
and here we are.

09:08.115 --> 09:11.284
Yeah, I don't think my mom and
dad will respond to that method.

09:11.284 --> 09:14.154
What if we threw their
anniversary party tonight?

09:14.154 --> 09:16.189
You know, I appreciate
the thought...

09:16.189 --> 09:17.324
A romantic dinner

09:17.324 --> 09:18.992
with music they like,

09:18.992 --> 09:22.062
and everything to remind them
of why they fell in love!

09:22.062 --> 09:24.632
Didi, if they're fine
with their decision,

09:24.632 --> 09:27.200
then we have to be, too.

09:27.200 --> 09:28.201
Okay.

09:28.201 --> 09:31.038
But maybe you should
just double-check.

09:31.038 --> 09:34.642
Make sure they really are fine.

09:34.642 --> 09:35.976
We are fine, son.

09:35.976 --> 09:38.779
People grow apart.
It happens.

09:38.779 --> 09:41.181
You just can't take it so hard.

09:41.181 --> 09:44.384
I just keep thinking maybe
it was something I did.

09:44.384 --> 09:46.219
No, of course not, Wade.

09:46.219 --> 09:48.521
Look, it'll work out
better for you.

09:48.521 --> 09:50.891
Two birthdays,
two Christmases.

09:50.891 --> 09:52.392
It's just so sad.

09:52.392 --> 09:56.396
You know, 40 years next month.

09:56.396 --> 09:59.199
Well, I'm sorry, son.

09:59.199 --> 10:02.035
Oh, it just breaks my heart
to see a good couple split up

10:02.035 --> 10:05.605
over something like,
"we grew apart."

10:07.540 --> 10:09.743
Marriage is complicated.

10:10.543 --> 10:13.981
Well, thanks for the beer, Wade.

10:18.218 --> 10:22.155
Yeah, well, enjoy it now,
'cause it ain't gonna last!

10:24.825 --> 10:26.559
(softly):
Ow.

10:26.559 --> 10:28.495
(clears throat)
Ow.

10:28.495 --> 10:31.498
Oh, there was
a lot of blood,
which surprised me.

10:31.498 --> 10:34.802
'Cause, you know,
I've heard you can't
get blood from a stone.

10:34.802 --> 10:36.670
Oh, ha-ha. Maybe you
should worry more

10:36.670 --> 10:39.707
about the stitches
and save your standup
routine for later.

10:39.707 --> 10:41.608
I'm gonna have
Addy take you

10:41.608 --> 10:43.143
to Mobile for a CT scan

10:43.143 --> 10:45.578
so we can rule out
a cerebral contusion

10:45.578 --> 10:47.781
Oh.
or... a bleed.

10:47.781 --> 10:50.951
You know, I don't
need a CT scan.

10:50.951 --> 10:53.386
All I need is a
nice, warm day...

10:53.386 --> 10:54.755
Whoa.
That's it.

10:54.755 --> 10:56.489
Addy, can you
come in here?

10:56.489 --> 10:57.858
(sighs)

10:57.858 --> 10:59.993
Oh, as your doctor--
or, sorry, at least

10:59.993 --> 11:02.730
as the person treating you--
I insist that you go home

11:02.730 --> 11:04.097
and lie down.
No.

11:04.097 --> 11:05.532
Addy, can you please
drive him home?

11:05.532 --> 11:07.801
I don't need
a ride home. I...
Oh, hush now,

11:07.801 --> 11:10.337
or I will whack you on the
other side of that head.

11:10.337 --> 11:12.472
Oh, hey, Addy.

11:12.472 --> 11:14.041
Hmm?
Was there a...?

11:14.041 --> 11:17.344
Oh, I'm sorry,
still no call from your dad.

11:22.082 --> 11:24.051
(quiet sigh)

11:25.085 --> 11:26.920
(sniffles)

11:28.021 --> 11:29.489
Mom.

11:29.489 --> 11:31.124
You okay?

11:31.124 --> 11:32.325
Oh, yeah.

11:32.325 --> 11:33.927
Just the onions, honey.

11:33.927 --> 11:36.329
You're not cutting onions.
Well, see, that's
why I'm crying--

11:36.329 --> 11:37.464
I really wanted onions.

11:37.464 --> 11:40.801
Mom, maybe this ain't
the right decision.

11:40.801 --> 11:42.402
Maybe you and Dad

11:42.402 --> 11:43.904
shouldn't be splitting up.

11:43.904 --> 11:45.172
Lavon, your father and I

11:45.172 --> 11:47.274
are just not
the couple we used to be.

11:48.175 --> 11:50.377
Doesn't mean
it isn't sad.

11:50.377 --> 11:52.145
Now, go wash up.

11:52.145 --> 11:53.413
Go on.

11:53.413 --> 11:54.948
(sniffles)

11:54.948 --> 11:58.385
(resumes chopping vegetables)

11:58.385 --> 11:59.652
LAVON:
Didi, Didi.

11:59.652 --> 12:01.221
You were right--
they're not okay.

12:01.221 --> 12:03.056
Call Wade,
'cause we're gonna

12:03.056 --> 12:05.759
throw my parents a big-ass
get-back-together party.

12:05.759 --> 12:07.527
Wow! All right!

12:07.527 --> 12:09.096
(laughing)

12:11.932 --> 12:15.035
Lemon? I got my suit,
got the rings.

12:15.035 --> 12:16.503
Your carriage awaits.

12:16.503 --> 12:18.105
Sweetheart,

12:18.105 --> 12:19.973
