let's hit the road.

12:39.960 --> 12:42.429
Shotgun!
No.
No.

12:42.429 --> 12:44.097
Well, hey, kids.

12:44.097 --> 12:45.432
What are y'all doing?

12:46.433 --> 12:48.101
Uh, it's a field trip.

12:48.101 --> 12:49.602
Yeah. A field trip.
Uh-huh.

12:49.602 --> 12:50.838
So, ladies,
we should...

12:50.838 --> 12:51.839
To the art museum!

12:51.839 --> 12:53.440
GEORGE:
Yeah. Art museum.

12:53.440 --> 12:55.242
Whoa, Daddy, what happened?

12:55.242 --> 12:57.777
Oh, you know, I banged my
head into a surfboard...

12:57.777 --> 13:02.482
No, it was a snowboard, and
I'm just gonna go lie down.

13:02.482 --> 13:06.386
You just all have
a good time at the museum.
Okay, Daddy, stop.

13:06.386 --> 13:09.857
Um... I have
to tell you something.

13:09.857 --> 13:11.291
Uh, so...

13:11.291 --> 13:13.560
George and I are
driving to Charleston...

13:13.560 --> 13:16.029
and we're getting
married in the morning.

13:16.029 --> 13:17.430
And Magnolia's

13:17.430 --> 13:18.698
coming with us.

13:18.698 --> 13:20.133
Will you come with us, too?

13:20.133 --> 13:21.768
BRICK:
Y-You're eloping?

13:21.768 --> 13:23.871
I-I mean, no church,

13:23.871 --> 13:26.106
no party, no...

13:26.106 --> 13:28.275
walking you
down the aisle?
Daddy, I'm
so sorry.

13:28.275 --> 13:30.010
I know that
this must be...

13:30.010 --> 13:32.579
really disappointing.

13:34.314 --> 13:35.482
Well...

13:36.449 --> 13:38.485
Not at all.

13:38.485 --> 13:39.619
Lemon-meringue,

13:39.619 --> 13:41.654
I would love
to go to Charleston.

13:41.654 --> 13:43.490
Really? (laughing)
Yeah.

13:43.490 --> 13:46.159
Oh, Daddy, thank you!

13:46.159 --> 13:47.560
Really, Brick?
Well, I mean,

13:47.560 --> 13:49.829
you two want to save me
thousands of dollars

13:49.829 --> 13:51.764
on a wedding,
hell, yes,

13:51.764 --> 13:53.700
be my guest.
But, uh,

13:53.700 --> 13:56.703
there's a couple of
things that I have
to take care of first.

13:56.703 --> 13:57.905
So, uh, just call me

13:57.905 --> 13:59.339
with the details,
and then
Okay.

13:59.339 --> 14:01.308
I'll meet you
there, okay?

14:01.308 --> 14:03.911
Great.
You know, I think
this is gonna be

14:03.911 --> 14:05.913
just... great.

14:05.913 --> 14:08.548
Oh, Daddy, I
love you so much.

14:08.548 --> 14:09.816
(car horn honks)

14:09.816 --> 14:11.484
Hold your horses,
I'm coming!

14:11.484 --> 14:12.986
(giggles)

14:13.820 --> 14:16.389
(door opens)

14:16.389 --> 14:18.691
(knocks)
Line two.
It's long distance.

14:18.691 --> 14:20.093
Europe!

14:21.661 --> 14:23.396
Hi, Daddy!

14:24.597 --> 14:27.267
Wait. I'm sorry,
I don't understand.

14:27.267 --> 14:28.835
What do you mean no one
named Ethan Hart

14:28.835 --> 14:30.270
lives at that address?

14:30.270 --> 14:32.405
He's my father-- I think
I know where he lives.

14:32.405 --> 14:33.873
What...?

14:33.873 --> 14:36.409
I see.

14:36.409 --> 14:38.878
(dial tone drones)

14:40.013 --> 14:42.115
Oh, Zoe, honey, I'm sorry.

14:42.115 --> 14:45.252
It's okay. It was
obviously a mistake.

14:45.252 --> 14:47.587
I mean, those stupid
German street names

14:47.587 --> 14:48.989
are so confusing.

14:48.989 --> 14:51.992
I'm just gonna have
to call my father myself.

14:51.992 --> 14:54.494
