new information

15:26.293 --> 15:28.461
to my old e-mail account
at New York Hospital!

15:28.461 --> 15:30.430
I'm gonna check it.
Uh, no, you won't.

15:30.430 --> 15:32.199
A big rig just
slid on the ice

15:32.199 --> 15:35.202
and smashed into the
pole that carries the
town's Internet cable.

15:36.869 --> 15:39.139
Okay. So, then, I...

15:39.139 --> 15:41.975
will sit here, steaming,

15:41.975 --> 15:44.911
because the hospital Web site
won't let you check your account

15:44.911 --> 15:46.679
(tosses cell phone)
from your cell phone!

15:46.679 --> 15:48.215
Damn it!

15:48.215 --> 15:52.185
I'm gonna get online somehow,
get to the bottom of this.

15:54.121 --> 15:56.756
Honey, why don't you wait
until tomorrow,

15:56.756 --> 15:57.857
when the snow'll stop

15:57.857 --> 15:59.292
bringing its bad luck.

15:59.292 --> 16:01.194
'Cause I am a scientist,
and scientists may have

16:01.194 --> 16:03.030
different theories on how
the dinosaurs died off,

16:03.030 --> 16:04.564
but not one of them

16:04.564 --> 16:07.367
ever said it's because
it was snowing that day.

16:08.168 --> 16:10.037
Because there was ice.

16:10.037 --> 16:11.071
If your parents

16:11.071 --> 16:12.239
are splitting up,

16:12.239 --> 16:14.107
why would they come
to a dinner party?

16:14.107 --> 16:17.510
I said I'm owed a final
dinner with my mom and
dad as a married couple!

16:17.510 --> 16:18.811
And then I kind of

16:18.811 --> 16:21.248
let my voice get all crackly
like I was choking back tears.

16:21.248 --> 16:22.582
DIDI:
I saw him.

16:22.582 --> 16:24.651
He milked it good.
Wait, maybe if
your parents

16:24.651 --> 16:26.919
have a favorite song,
I could learn it,

16:26.919 --> 16:28.388
and then, like, uh, you know...

16:28.388 --> 16:30.457
serenade 'em with it.

16:30.457 --> 16:32.792
Yeah, yeah. Uh,
"Kiss an Angel Good Morning"

16:32.792 --> 16:34.094
was their wedding song.

16:34.094 --> 16:36.463
Do they have a favorite
by Tom Petty?

16:36.463 --> 16:39.032
I'm gonna make
my famous spaghetti.

16:39.032 --> 16:40.333
Maybe they'll
share a bowl

16:40.333 --> 16:42.669
and end up sucking on
the same piece of pasta,

16:42.669 --> 16:43.936
like those dogs.

16:43.936 --> 16:46.906
Everybody should probably
have their own bowl of pasta.

16:46.906 --> 16:48.341
But I appreciate
the sentiment, though.

16:48.341 --> 16:50.210
Oh, do you have any
old pictures of them?

16:50.210 --> 16:52.212
Nothing makes a couple
get all gooey emotional

16:52.212 --> 16:54.047
like seeing themselves
together back in the day.

16:54.047 --> 16:57.217
Oh, oh, you know what, I have
some of their old slides.
Perfect!

16:57.217 --> 16:59.186
We can have a This
 Is Your Marriage show.

16:59.186 --> 17:00.387
I saw it on Dr. Phil.

17:00.387 --> 17:01.621
We'll show
them pictures

17:01.621 --> 17:03.490
of their wedding,
their honeymoon,

17:03.490 --> 17:06.093
their children,
everything that'll remind them

17:06.093 --> 17:07.827
of why they're
still together.

17:07.827 --> 17:10.963
Didi,you are a genius.

17:10.963 --> 17:12.098
Really.

17:12.098 --> 17:14.032
It isn't said enough.

17:14.032 --> 17:16.336
I know I've never heard it.

17:22.040 --> 17:23.542
Oh, hey.

17:23.542 --> 17:24.777
(shivers)

17:24.777 --> 17:26.113
Hey, Norbert.

17:26.113 --> 17:27.980
Hey, Doc.
Oh...

17:27.980 --> 17:30.817
Hey, listen...

17:30.817 --> 17:32.119
Whoa.
(laughs)

17:32.119 --> 17:35.855
Well, listen, I have
this, uh, vintage veil...

17:35.855 --> 17:37.924
Is that the right
word, "veil"?

17:37.924 --> 17:39.526
Anyway, it belonged

17:39.526 --> 17:43.396
to my mother, and I
want to give it to
my daughter, Magnolia,

17:43.396 --> 17:45.265
