21:33.926 --> 21:35.628
(door slams shut)

21:35.628 --> 21:39.566
This is not how
it went on Dr. Phil.

21:48.875 --> 21:50.777
You want to tell me
what Dad was talking about?

21:53.346 --> 21:54.881
I have, um...

21:54.881 --> 21:58.217
reconnected, through Facebook,
with a high school boyfriend,

21:58.217 --> 21:59.419
Dwayne.

21:59.419 --> 22:03.255
How long has this,
uh, reconnection

22:03.255 --> 22:06.359
with Dwayne been going on?

22:06.359 --> 22:08.361
About a year.

22:08.361 --> 22:10.630
Your father found out
a few weeks ago,

22:10.630 --> 22:12.932
insisted that I cut off all
communications with him.

22:12.932 --> 22:15.001
Your father--
I mean, I can't
tell you the last time

22:15.001 --> 22:16.803
he looked up at me
from the sports pages,

22:16.803 --> 22:20.407
let alone, you know,
take me out on a date.

22:20.407 --> 22:22.274
I thought every Friday
you two go out?

22:22.274 --> 22:24.711
Bowling is not a date.

22:24.711 --> 22:29.849
I mean, we talked about jetting
off to the South Pacific.

22:29.849 --> 22:34.186
Now it's all about
the restaurant

22:34.186 --> 22:36.589
and whose turn it is to
unload the dishwasher.
Okay.

22:36.589 --> 22:38.558
So, you hit a rough patch.

22:38.558 --> 22:40.993
No need to turn
to somebody else.

22:40.993 --> 22:45.832
Dwayne makes me feel alive

22:45.832 --> 22:49.201
and young, like I
did in high school,

22:49.201 --> 22:51.103
I thought he was my true love.

22:51.103 --> 22:54.040
I know, honey, it's hard
for you to understand; I...

22:54.040 --> 22:55.408
No.

22:55.408 --> 22:57.444
Actually, it's not.

22:57.444 --> 22:59.078
Please, honey, just
go find your father.

22:59.078 --> 23:01.914
I don't want him out there
on the road in the snow.

23:01.914 --> 23:03.916
(quietly):
Okay.

