24:38.978 --> 24:40.379
People freeze to
death in their cars.

24:40.379 --> 24:43.082
Okay, you know, rarely on
the Gulf Coast of Alabama,

24:43.082 --> 24:45.552
and never on a 20-minute
walk from their own home.

24:45.552 --> 24:47.920
Magnolia, you
just don't seem

24:47.920 --> 24:49.722
very positive about all this.

24:49.722 --> 24:51.958
Why did you even want to
come in the first place?

24:51.958 --> 24:54.426
Because you promised I
could be the maid of honor.

24:54.426 --> 24:55.562
Well, sweetheart, you are.

24:55.562 --> 24:57.496
In a wedding.

24:57.496 --> 25:00.800
I wanted to wear a poofy dress,

25:00.800 --> 25:02.935
to be in all the pictures

25:02.935 --> 25:06.839
right next to you, right up
in front of the whole church!

25:06.839 --> 25:11.010
Everyone in school
was gonna be jealous.

25:11.010 --> 25:13.946
But mostly,

25:13.946 --> 25:17.183
I wanted to be with you
on your wedding day.

25:17.183 --> 25:20.587
To see you all

25:20.587 --> 25:22.188
glowing and crap.

25:22.188 --> 25:24.557
That's what I wanted.

25:24.557 --> 25:27.760
Aw, sweetheart.

25:29.461 --> 25:30.697
I love you, baby.

25:30.697 --> 25:31.998
It'll be good, okay?

25:31.998 --> 25:36.468
(sighs) Okay, so the
gas station's closed,

25:36.468 --> 25:37.737
of course,

25:37.737 --> 25:39.371
because the pumps are broken,

25:39.371 --> 25:42.208
so... no battery.

25:42.208 --> 25:43.910
(car approaches)

25:51.483 --> 25:52.952
Everything all right?

25:52.952 --> 25:55.655
Uh, you know what,
actually, it's not.

25:55.655 --> 25:58.658
We could use a jump.

26:03.195 --> 26:04.496
Mom, it's me.

26:04.496 --> 26:06.032
Listen, something really
weird happened,

26:06.032 --> 26:08.434
I tried to send Dad
something in Germany,

26:08.434 --> 26:10.536
and he's not at his old address.

26:10.536 --> 26:12.138
His phone's been disconnected.

26:12.138 --> 26:15.407
I'm getting worried
that something might've hap...

26:15.407 --> 26:18.611
What do you mean
you ran into him?

26:20.546 --> 26:23.750
He moved back to New York?

26:25.351 --> 26:27.920
Yeah, no, that must've been
an awkward conversation.

26:27.920 --> 26:30.589
Talk to you later, Mom.

26:30.589 --> 26:32.792
(clears throat)

26:34.560 --> 26:35.828
You okay, Dr. Hart?

26:35.828 --> 26:38.230
Huh? Yeah, thanks.
Well, good.

26:38.230 --> 26:40.800
(wry laugh) This town doesn't
need both doctors out of whack.

26:40.800 --> 26:42.669
You know, Doc Breeland came

26:42.669 --> 26:43.870
to see me earlier.

26:43.870 --> 26:45.604
Boy, was he out of it.

26:46.338 --> 26:48.140
Must be the snow.

26:48.140 --> 26:50.142
See you.

26:53.245 --> 26:55.948
(car starts)
All right.

26:55.948 --> 26:58.384
All right,
jumper cables.

26:58.384 --> 27:00.386
Should just about do it.

27:04.023 --> 27:05.758
You going somewhere special?

27:05.758 --> 27:10.096
I mean, you don't really want
to be out on a night like this.

27:10.096 --> 27:12.098
(sighing)

27:14.333 --> 27:16.568
Actually...

27:16.568 --> 27:18.971
George and I are eloping.

27:21.173 --> 27:23.175
Are you?

27:23.175 --> 27:26.846
We're driving to Charleston.

27:26.846 --> 27:28.681
We're getting married
first thing in the morning.

27:28.681 --> 27:30.783
Well, good for you.

27:32.919 --> 27:35.554
You know, that...
night back in December

27:35.554 --> 27:37.589
when I came to your house,

27:37.589 --> 27:40.426
and you wouldn't let me in?

27:40.426 --> 27:44.096
You were right.

27:44.096 --> 27:47.566
I went and told George
about finding my mother,

27:47.566 --> 27:50.269
and he was just...

27:50.269 --> 27:52.471
He was wonderful.

27:52.471 --> 27:55.141
And...

27:55.141 --> 27:57.243
We've never been closer.

27:57.243 --> 28:01.347
(exhales)
I'm glad you're happy.

28:07.153 --> 28:09.355
Well, I wish you all the best.

28:14.761 --> 28:16.662
All right.

28:16.662 --> 28:18.931
Well, Lavon, we cannot
thank you enough.

28:18.931 --> 28:20.366
LEMON:
Yes, thank you.

28:20.366 --> 28:22.168
LAVON:
Drive safe.

28:22.168 --> 28:24.136
Thank you.

28:25.237 --> 28:27.239
For everything.

28:31.610 --> 28:33.079
(truck door closes)

28:46.125 --> 28:47.059
(knocking)

28:47.059 --> 28:48.627
ZOE:
Anybody home?

28:48.627 --> 28:49.829
(knocks)

28:51.397 --> 28:53.499
Hello? Brick?

28:53.499 --> 28:55.167
(groaning)

28:55.167 --> 28:57.036
Brick?

29:00.439 --> 29:01.908
Mama, we need to talk, okay?

29:01.908 --> 29:03.109
Did you find your father?

29:03.109 --> 29:04.276
Yeah. He's with Wade,
getting drunk,

29:04.276 --> 29:06.245
talking about
God knows what.

29:06.245 --> 29:07.980
But you need to end things
with this Dwayne guy.

29:07.980 --> 29:10.116
What? Honey, I thought
you understood.

29:10.116 --> 29:12.151
What I understand
is that in real life,

29:12.151 --> 29:13.886
you don't always
get be with the one

29:13.886 --> 29:15.822
who makes your heart
pound or your knees weak.

29:15.822 --> 29:17.857
Okay? No, real life
is about

29:17.857 --> 29:21.127
being with a person
that you can make a life with.

29:21.127 --> 29:23.362
Someone who's attainable.

29:23.362 --> 29:26.198
Someone you have something
in common with.

29:26.198 --> 29:27.566
Like...

29:27.566 --> 29:28.868
bowling.

29:28.868 --> 29:30.937
True love...

29:32.138 --> 29:33.605
True love is a fantasy.

29:33.605 --> 29:35.374
Even if Dad is not everything

29:35.374 --> 29:37.609
that you thought
you wanted, he's real.

29:37.609 --> 29:41.047
Okay? He's there.

29:41.047 --> 29:43.315
You got to make that work.

29:44.616 --> 29:46.518
(door opens)

29:46.518 --> 29:48.955
Hey, hey, I'm sorry
to interrupt y'all.

29:48.955 --> 29:50.289
Uh, it's Ernie.

29:50.289 --> 29:51.924
There's, uh, a bit
of a situation.

29:51.924 --> 29:53.692
Y'all better come with me.

29:53.692 --> 29:54.894
Now.

29:56.628 --> 29:58.764
Why can't you
just answer?

29:58.764 --> 29:59.932
Where is Ernie?

29:59.932 --> 30:01.367
What the hell
is going on, Wade?

30:01.367 --> 30:02.835
(clears throat)
Oh, I'm not Wade.

30:02.835 --> 30:05.671
I'm your bellhop, Dade.

30:05.671 --> 30:08.875
Ma'am, your suite awaits.

30:11.777 --> 30:14.246
What is all this?

30:27.159 --> 30:30.829
You always wanted
to go to Bora Bora.

30:30.829 --> 30:33.933
Look,

30:33.933 --> 30:37.036
I'm sorry I gave you
that ultimatum

30:37.036 --> 30:39.305
about breaking things
off with Dwayne.

30:39.305 --> 30:41.407
Dwayne wasn't the problem.

30:41.407 --> 30:43.342
I was.

30:43.342 --> 30:45.611
Ernie, I...
No, no, Carolyn,

30:45.611 --> 30:49.148
Our relationship needed
just as much of my attention

30:49.148 --> 30:51.083
and devotion as I gave
to the restaurant

30:51.083 --> 30:53.920
and the Crimson Tide.

30:53.920 --> 30:55.621
I blew it.

30:55.621 --> 30:58.490
Now, I... I'll pick my
socks up off the floor.

30:58.490 --> 31:01.961
I'll even take
ballroom dancing.

31:01.961 --> 31:07.133
Sweetheart, you are
my one true love.

31:07.133 --> 31:11.971
And I will do anything

31:11.971 --> 31:14.440
for a second chance.

31:14.440 --> 31:17.243
It was Fiji.

31:17.243 --> 31:19.878
I always wanted to go to Fiji.

31:19.878 --> 31:21.413
(chuckles)

31:22.848 --> 31:24.416
But this is close enough.

31:26.852 --> 31:28.487
(click)

31:28.487 --> 31:30.489
* *

31:34.393 --> 31:36.028
(whispering):
Dance with her.

31:46.072 --> 31:47.839
That's me.

31:47.839 --> 31:50.476
WADE: Who would
have figured?

31:50.476 --> 31:52.478
I'm a damn cupid.

32:01.087 --> 32:03.022
(door closes)

32:03.855 --> 32:05.091
I-I don't know what happened.

32:05.091 --> 32:06.825
I was... I was...
heading up the upstairs,

32:06.825 --> 32:11.397
and I... oh, I got dizzy,
and-and I... I lost my balance.

32:11.397 --> 32:14.466
Okay. Well, a few hours ago, you
had a significant head injury.

32:14.466 --> 32:16.135
And now you're trying
to climb a ladder?

32:16.135 --> 32:17.603
Seriously, you need to lie down.

32:17.603 --> 32:18.971
No, I... I got to get going.

32:18.971 --> 32:21.207
I got to be
in-in Charleston by 8:00 a.m.

32:21.207 --> 32:23.209
Whoa. Hey,
there. No, no.

32:23.209 --> 32:25.177
You, my friend, are
not going anywhere.

32:25.177 --> 32:27.446
No. Of course I am, 'cause
Lemon and-and George--

32:27.446 --> 32:30.882
they are... they are halfway
to, um-- what-you-ma-call-it?

32:30.882 --> 32:32.351
Yeah, now, South...
South Africa.

32:32.351 --> 32:33.319
Pardon?

32:33.319 --> 32:35.021
Look, I mean
South Carolina.

32:35.021 --> 32:36.922
They are eloping.

32:36.922 --> 32:38.324
Eloping?

32:38.324 --> 32:39.558
Yeah.

32:39.558 --> 32:42.028
As in, getting married
quicker than we thought?

32:42.028 --> 32:44.096
Well, yes, that is
the definition of eloping.

32:44.096 --> 32:48.600
Well, that's...
good for them.

32:48.600 --> 32:51.237
Wait. Brick, you can
barely walk, okay?

32:51.237 --> 32:53.639
You are not driving
to South Carolina

32:53.639 --> 32:55.907
or South Africa or anywhere.

32:55.907 --> 32:58.410
(sighs)

33:02.214 --> 33:05.117
How far is it to
flipping South Carolina?

33:05.117 --> 33:06.252
It is far.

33:06.252 --> 33:08.354
Do you have
to hit every bump?

33:08.354 --> 33:10.656
I mean, I have
such a nasty headache.

33:10.656 --> 33:12.624
Because you probably
have a mild concussion,

33:12.624 --> 33:15.094
which is why we should be
taking you to a hospital.

33:15.094 --> 33:16.962
No!
Seriously, Brick,
I don't get it.

33:16.962 --> 33:18.297
I know Lemon is eloping,

33:18.297 --> 33:20.532
but is it really worth
risking your own health?

33:20.532 --> 33:23.435
I have been waiting
for my little girl's wedding

33:23.435 --> 33:25.271
since she was two weeks old.

33:25.271 --> 33:28.107
I would not miss it
for anything.

33:28.107 --> 33:30.409
When you have kids, you'll see.

33:30.409 --> 33:32.811
All parents feel this way.

33:32.811 --> 33:35.581
Not all parents.

33:37.816 --> 33:40.186
Well, maybe you're right.

33:41.253 --> 33:43.855
But if it's any consolation,

33:43.855 --> 33:46.058
it's his loss.

34:00.939 --> 34:02.641
LEMON:
Sorry, honey.

34:02.641 --> 34:05.144
The restroom of a city park
is not the most convenient place

34:05.144 --> 34:06.945
to put on
a wedding dress, but...

34:06.945 --> 34:09.081
MAGNOLIA:
There was a woman in there,
with the tiniest skirt

34:09.081 --> 34:12.618
and tallest heels I've ever
seen, counting a lot of money.

34:12.618 --> 34:13.952
Whatever job she has,

34:13.952 --> 34:15.154
that's the one I want.

34:15.154 --> 34:17.255
Uh-uh.
Well, you...

34:17.255 --> 34:18.524
both look very beautiful.

34:18.524 --> 34:20.891
Now, as soon as
your dad gets here,

34:20.891 --> 34:23.495
we can get in
and get started.
Well, he's not here yet?

34:23.495 --> 34:25.831
Well, I mean, you don't
want to go through this

34:25.831 --> 34:27.399
without him, do you?

34:27.399 --> 34:29.868
Look, if we have to, we
just... we just reschedule.

34:29.868 --> 34:31.270
MAGNOLIA:
There he is!

34:31.270 --> 34:33.772
Folks, I'm so sorry
this drive took me longer

34:33.772 --> 34:37.309
than I thought,
but I'm here now, okay?

34:37.309 --> 34:38.444
Daddy.
Daddy.

34:38.444 --> 34:39.777
BRICK:
So, let's do it, huh?

34:39.777 --> 34:40.879
Yeah.

34:40.879 --> 34:42.981
Ugh, this place
smells like pee.

34:42.981 --> 34:44.116
LEMON:
Yes, it does.

34:44.116 --> 34:45.451
MAGNOLIA:
I just don't get it.

34:45.451 --> 34:47.585
This is how people want
to get married?

34:47.585 --> 34:49.455
It's gross.

34:49.455 --> 34:51.623
Wait.

34:51.623 --> 34:53.592
I can't...

34:54.693 --> 34:56.695
...do this.
I agree with Magnolia.

34:56.695 --> 34:59.431
What-what are
you saying?
It's just
a funky-smelling courthouse

34:59.431 --> 35:02.701
and a-a judge
we don't even know?

35:04.203 --> 35:05.437
I don't want that.

35:05.437 --> 35:08.073
Lemon, I want a real wedding.

35:08.073 --> 35:09.841
Oh, my God,
you are such a girl.

35:09.841 --> 35:11.009
Magnolia.

35:11.009 --> 35:12.311
You know what? I don't...

35:12.311 --> 35:15.046
I don't care how it sounds,
because I do.

35:15.046 --> 35:16.582
I want a real... wedding.

35:16.582 --> 35:18.717
I want my brother
to be there,

35:18.717 --> 35:21.052
and I want my parents
to be there.

35:21.052 --> 35:22.654
I want my niece
to be the flower girl

35:22.654 --> 35:24.256
like we said
she was gonna be.

35:24.256 --> 35:26.925
Hell, I-I want my...
my bachelor hunting trip.

35:26.925 --> 35:28.560
Come on.

35:28.560 --> 35:30.696
But Lemon,
most importantly,

35:30.696 --> 35:33.332
I don't want to miss out
on the chance

35:33.332 --> 35:38.404
to see the single most beautiful
bride in the world

35:38.404 --> 35:40.339
walking down that aisle
towards me.

35:40.339 --> 35:42.641
(Lemon laughs)

35:42.641 --> 35:44.243
I want a real
wedding, too.

35:44.243 --> 35:46.445
I do. I do.
(laughing)

35:46.445 --> 35:47.913
BRICK
Thank God,

35:47.913 --> 35:49.181
'cause I want
one, too!

35:49.181 --> 35:51.350
I want a really
big washing!

35:51.350 --> 35:52.751
A wedding. Wedding.
What did I say?

35:52.751 --> 35:55.487
A wedding. That's what I
want for my little girl.

35:55.487 --> 35:58.089
You know, and... and
I want some aspirin.

35:58.089 --> 35:59.958
Yeah, of course.

35:59.958 --> 36:02.394
Oh.

36:03.962 --> 36:06.498
(laughing):
Morning, son.

36:06.498 --> 36:07.933
CAROLYN:
Morning, baby.

36:07.933 --> 36:09.167
Hey, hey, you two.

36:09.167 --> 36:11.603
How was, uh, Bora Bora,

36:11.603 --> 36:13.805
or Fiji, or wherever
y'all went?

36:13.805 --> 36:16.107
It was just as you'd
expect the tropics--

36:16.107 --> 36:17.976
hot and steamy.

36:17.976 --> 36:19.678
Mmm.

36:19.678 --> 36:21.680
(kissing sounds)

36:21.680 --> 36:25.050
Okay, yeah, well,
that's, um, um,

36:25.050 --> 36:27.052
all I need to hear.

36:27.052 --> 36:29.255
Wherever we were,
it was divine.

36:29.255 --> 36:32.123
Your father and I...
found the romance again.

36:32.123 --> 36:33.292
That we did.

36:33.292 --> 36:34.726
Mm-hmm.

36:34.726 --> 36:36.395
I'm glad.

36:36.395 --> 36:38.964
Hey, honeymoon suite

36:38.964 --> 36:41.833
also comes with complimentary

36:41.833 --> 36:42.901
brunch.

36:42.901 --> 36:44.670
CAROLYN:
Honey, brunch
sounds wonderful.

36:44.670 --> 36:48.374
Hey, um, listen,
I'll be right back.

36:48.374 --> 36:50.309
I want to say
good-bye to Wade.

36:50.309 --> 36:51.643
(laughter)

36:51.643 --> 36:54.280
CAROLYN:
Lavon, I just wanted
to let you know

36:54.280 --> 36:56.548
that, um, I'm going
to unfriend Dwayne.

36:56.548 --> 36:58.417
Well, I think
that's a good idea.

36:58.417 --> 37:02.954
But son, what you said to me
last night has me worried.

37:02.954 --> 37:05.491
I mean, marriage is hard.

37:05.491 --> 37:07.493
Your father and
I, you know,

37:07.493 --> 37:09.961
fell into the same trap
a lot of people do.

37:09.961 --> 37:13.231
I mean, it's easy to fantasize
about being with someone else.

37:13.231 --> 37:16.302
But that's all it
was, was a fantasy.

37:16.302 --> 37:20.306
Your father and I--
that's the real deal.

37:20.306 --> 37:22.974
Hard as it may be sometimes,

37:22.974 --> 37:25.777
he is my true love.

37:27.145 --> 37:29.147
That's great.

37:29.147 --> 37:30.949
I'm glad
you guys have each other.

37:30.949 --> 37:34.953
All that hullabaloo about
true love being a fantasy

37:34.953 --> 37:39.758
just leads me to believe
you might not be with yours.

37:39.758 --> 37:41.760
Hmm?

37:42.694 --> 37:44.896
(whispers):
Love you, babe.

38:08.086 --> 38:10.856
Oh. Hey.

38:10.856 --> 38:12.758
Uh, I-I can explain.

38:12.758 --> 38:15.494
You know what?
It doesn't matter.

38:15.494 --> 38:17.363
I'm too tired to care.

38:17.363 --> 38:19.030
Well, let's
just say, I, uh,

38:19.030 --> 38:21.099
helped get Lavon's
parents back together.

38:21.099 --> 38:24.035
Which they did... in my bed.

38:24.035 --> 38:26.638
Well, no, I wa...
I-I changed the sheets already.

38:27.806 --> 38:29.808
Yeah.

38:31.843 --> 38:34.045
Uh, by the way,

38:34.045 --> 38:39.117
I'm sorry if I'm the reason
that you and Judson broke up.

38:39.117 --> 38:42.388
I shouldn't
have butted in.

38:42.388 --> 38:45.457
I don't know. Everyone's talking
about true love, and...

38:45.457 --> 38:47.626
well, if Judson was
your true love, then...

38:47.626 --> 38:49.395
he'll come back.

38:51.863 --> 38:53.732
For the record,

38:53.732 --> 38:56.935
Judson was not my true love.

39:00.071 --> 39:03.709
Anyway, a package arrived
for you "return to sender."

39:14.019 --> 39:15.821
We made it.

39:15.821 --> 39:20.258
We survived a BlueBell snow day
without any huge disasters.

39:20.258 --> 39:22.461
(laughs)

39:28.166 --> 39:31.169
Didi...

39:31.169 --> 39:34.239
I don't think you and I
should keep seeing each other.

39:34.239 --> 39:37.375
You're kidding, right?

39:37.375 --> 39:40.045
I wanted to-to make
this work, I really did.

39:40.045 --> 39:42.047
I thought I could, but...

39:42.047 --> 39:44.850
I'm just not ready.

39:45.684 --> 39:47.919
I wish you had told me earlier.

39:48.920 --> 39:51.389
I wish I had known.

39:51.389 --> 39:55.761
You are an amazing
woman, Didi Ruano.

39:57.128 --> 40:00.766
I can't thank you enough for
what you did with my parents,

40:00.766 --> 40:02.734
but I have been unfair to you.

40:02.734 --> 40:07.138
I'm sorry. Last thing I ever
wanted to do was hurt you.

40:08.173 --> 40:09.975
It's a little late for that.

40:13.612 --> 40:16.448
See you around, Lavon.

40:23.188 --> 40:25.524
* *

40:31.463 --> 40:32.964
Hi.

40:32.964 --> 40:34.165
Hey.

40:34.165 --> 40:35.366
How was your snow day?

40:35.366 --> 40:37.769
Oh, to sum up:

40:37.769 --> 40:41.707
My parents didn't break up,
Didi and I did,

40:41.707 --> 40:45.110
and I helped Lemon
and George elope.

40:45.110 --> 40:47.145
(laughs)
Yours?

40:47.145 --> 40:50.181
My dad was not kidnapped,

40:50.181 --> 40:53.685
my dad still sucks, and you
didn't help them elope.

40:55.286 --> 40:57.556
They-they didn't do it?

40:59.658 --> 41:01.593
Sorry about Didi.

41:01.593 --> 41:03.795
Um, sorry about your dad.

41:03.795 --> 41:06.331
Hey, on the bright side...

